HEADWORD: Futurism
<hw>Fu"tur*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Painting)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A movement or phase of post-impressionism (which see,
below).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A point of view that finds meaning or fulfillment in
the future rather than in the past or present. The philosophy of a
<er>futurist</er>.</def> <au>MW10</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Futurist</ent>⟦br⟧
